parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to sink to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibrations, noise, and uneven braking, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or rubbing noise when applying the brakes
vibrations when braking
uneven braking
or excessive wear on brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can cause uneven braking, noise, and vibrations, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or rubbing noise when applying the brakes
vibrations when braking
uneven braking
or excessive wear on brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the engine continues to rev even after the vehicle is stopped
or the vehicle takes off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brakes make a grinding or rubbing noise
or the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks and sludge can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: Oil leaks
blue smoke from the tailpipe
excessive oil consumption
engine failure
and smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and seizure can cause accidents, fires, and costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine failure
seizure
loss of power
and smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause accidents, fires, and costly repairs.
symptoms: Electrical system failure
faulty throttle position sensor
faulty idle speed control valve
and smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air induction hose failure can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: Cracking of the air induction hose
difficulty starting the engine
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission failure can cause accidents, costly repairs, and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and without warning
sometimes after slowing down or stopping
and the brakes may not respond or may be ineffective in stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck or hard to press
sometimes requiring extra force to release
and may cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or sluggish acceleration can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lag, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging or crossing traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer than expected to accelerate
or may hesitate or lag when the accelerator pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to engage or disengage properly
or causes the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to premature wear on other components.
symptoms: Clunking
banging
rattling
or squeaking noises when driving over bumps or uneven surfaces
especially when cold. The noise may be temperature-dependent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to bottom out, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle bottoms out when driving over dips
bumps
or uneven surfaces
especially when carrying passengers or cargo.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the struts can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to premature wear on other components.
symptoms: Leaking struts
noisy struts
or failure of the strut mounts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer bar can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to premature wear on other components.
symptoms: The stabilizer bar splits or breaks
causing a loss of control.
